UESMS - Trace Analyzer
 
First commercial release of the Trace Analyzer is going to be released soon!

The evaluation of the product has started with some of our specific customers. If you feel that your company would be a suitable candidate into our testing team, don't hesitate to contact Trace Analyzer product owner, Ville Kukonlehto.

Trace Analyzer is a tool for analyzing and integrating massive amount of data from various different sources. When you have a lot of data recorded from various different sources (e.g. from UE, nodeB, RNC, etc.) and you need to see the overall picture of different processes, Trace Analyzer can show all of that data in one view. Different data files are also synchronized together.

Sharing findings and information between different groups is easier than ever before, with Trace Analyzer documentation function. You can document your findings into analysis, and all findings are tied to a time stamp, so it will be seen in specific row of data view.

Automating routine work! All findings, filters and analysis variables can be stored into a computer and shared easily with your colleagues. Any or all of these stored features can be automated, e.g. all of the chosen features are executed automatically when creating new analysis.

There will be 3 different versions of the Trace Analyzer:

Trace Analyzer Pro is the most comprehensive version, and it is targeted to customers who are developing rapid, real-time embedded systems. User can work with log-files in maximum precision and with complete set of Trace Analyzer features.  

Trace Analyzer Lite is targeted to customers who does not need to deal with real-time systems (e.g. web-server administrators). The work with the log-files is with limited time precision (1 sec.) and specifically selected set of Trace Analyzer features.

Trace Analyzer Reader is designed to customers who need to be able to read the created analysis report. Trace Analyzer Reader can be used to view the results of the problem analysis for example by the company's management if they need to stay in touch with the processes . Analysis result report is transferable with one's partner if he/she does not have Trace Analyzer Pro/Lite.
 
Trace Analyzer Reader is free of charge and can be downloaded from our web-site (after release).
